<p>These searches have immediate intent. The person searching "emergency vet near me" at 11 PM is calling the first result they see.</p>
<h3>Content Keywords That Build Authority</h3>
<p>For blog content, target questions pet owners search before and after vet visits:</p>
<ul>
<li>"how often should I take my dog to the vet"</li>
<li>"what vaccines does my puppy need"</li>
<li>"is [food/plant] toxic to dogs"</li>
<li>"why is my cat throwing up"</li>
<li>"how much does [procedure] cost for a dog"</li>
</ul>
<p>Each of these becomes a blog post that builds <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> around veterinary care topics. Google starts treating your site as a trusted source on pet health, which lifts rankings across all your pages.</p>
