<h3>5 Content Types That Work for Vet SEO</h3>
<p><strong>1. Condition guides</strong> (highest volume)
"Why Is My Dog Limping? 7 Causes and What to Do". These rank for thousands of symptom-related searches. Write one per common condition.</p>
<p><strong>2. Cost transparency pages</strong> (highest conversion)
"How Much Does Dog Teeth Cleaning Cost in [City]?". Pet owners search costs before calling. Be the practice that answers honestly.</p>
<p><strong>3. Service pages</strong> (local ranking power)
One dedicated page per service. "Dog Vaccinations in [City]" ranks better than a generic "Services" page that lists everything.</p>
<p><strong>4. Breed-specific care guides</strong> (zero competition)
"French Bulldog Health Issues: What Every Owner Should Know". Breed-specific content attracts dedicated pet owners with zero competition from other vet clinics.</p>
<p><strong>5. Seasonal pet safety content</strong> (timely traffic spikes)
"4th of July Fireworks: How to Keep Your Dog Calm". Seasonal content captures massive search spikes at predictable times each year.</p>
<h3>Publishing Frequency</h3>
<p>Consistency beats intensity. Clinics that publish 4 or more blog posts per month build <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> faster than those publishing once per month. A regular <a href="/blog/create-content-calendar-seo/">content calendar</a> ensures steady output without last-minute scrambling.</p>
